---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PasswordChecker from '../../components/PasswordChecker';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Password Strength Checker | Free Online Tool"
  description="Test your password strength with our free checker. See estimated crack time, get a detailed security checklist, and learn how to create strong passwords."
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-gray-900">Password Strength Checker</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-gray-600">
        Type a password to see how strong it really is. Get an estimated crack time, a checklist of what makes a good password, and practical tips for improvement.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-4 inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full bg-accent-50 px-4 py-1.5 text-sm font-medium text-accent-700">
        🔒 Your password is processed entirely in your browser — it is never sent anywhere
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-6 sm:p-10 shadow-sm">
      <PasswordChecker client:load />
    </div>

    <div class="mx-auto mt-12 max-w-2xl prose prose-gray">
      <h2>What Makes a Strong Password?</h2>
      <p>A strong password has three characteristics:</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Length:</strong> At least 12 characters. The longer, the better — each additional character makes cracking exponentially harder.</li>
        <li><strong>Complexity:</strong> Mix uppercase letters, lowercase letters, numbers, and special characters.</li>
        <li><strong>Uniqueness:</strong> Never reuse passwords across accounts. If one site gets breached, all your accounts are vulnerable.</li>
      </ol>
      <p>The best password is one you do not need to remember. Use a password manager like Bitwarden or 1Password to generate and store strong, unique passwords for every account.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
